<br>
IMO, for any class the most important RAs are Purge and IP. What it comes down to is that all the other RAs are meaningless if you are either A) Dead, or B) Incapacitated (Mezzed, Stunned, Paralyzed, Rooted). Both IP and Purge directly affect how long you are alive and active in a battle; and while in zerg warfare it rarely determines the outcome of the battle in small warfare it will often make the difference between victory and defeat.<br>
<br>
Purge: Yes, another class can cure mez but this is dependant on several things. First, they have to be alive to unmez you. Second, they have to realize you're mezzed, third they need to be within range. And lastly if they are mezzed too, then you're outta luck. Also, I'm unsure of this, but I think the cure mez spell is a spell and not an insta-cast. Hence if they are being attacked, they can't unmez you and you can't help get the attacker off of them. I'd consider purge having a higher value than IP, as if you're stunned you can't IP.<br>
<br>
IP: This allows for the fight to last longer and hopefully you kill off your attacker before you are killed. Like purge, this really doesn't impact the outcomes of zerg warfare. However, it does have a direct corrolation to the success of small group warfare.<br>
<br>
Unforunately both of these RAs are extremely expensive. Purge 10, and IP 23 (including FA2 prereq) Therefore they should be among the first RAs that you get since the realm points are easier to get at the lower Realm Ranks.  From RR5 to RR6 it takes on average 50krps to gain one realm level, and to go from RR6 to RR7 it takes on average 75krps per realm level.<br>
<br>
I'm probably one of the few skalds that doesn't have MCL, and don't have any intention on getting it. I can't justify spending realm points on items that I can buy with bounty points. While most people complain about the bounty totems being worthless, I seriously doubt that most of these people have even tried them. The power totem gives about 25%/30% power back and a totem can be used every 3 minutes. So essentially the power restoration of a totem is equivilant to MCL1; additionally you can use a totem every three minutes as opposed to five minutes. The same thing applies to Second Wind, albeit a little different as this RA is extremely expensive considering the Aug Con 3 prereq.<br>
<br>
The order I chose for RAs is as follows:<br>
1. RA Essentials<br>
2. Increase Damage Output<br>
3. Increase Defensive Skills<br>
<br>
